edgment Logic** (Partition.scala): The appendRecordsToLeader method (line 1361-1375) checks if the ISR size meets the minimum ISR requirement when requiredAcks == -1 (acks=all). The checkEnoughReplicasReachOffset method (line 1089-1123) verifies that enough replicas have reached the required offset by checking the high watermark and in-sync replicas.\n\n8. **Delayed Operation Management** (DelayedProduce.scala): The ProduceMetadata class (line 43) stores the produceRequiredAcks value. The DelayedProduce operation (line 57-135) monitors partition acknowledgment status via the tryComplete method (line 89-117), which checks if enough replicas have acknowledged the write using partition.checkEnoughReplicasReachOffset."
